1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,980
=Wonder Wall=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,910
=Episode 13=

3
00:01:47,319 --> 00:01:48,280
What is he doing here?

4
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:49,159
What is going on?

5
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,040
No idea.

6
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:52,319
This is mine.

7
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:53,560
My money.

8
00:01:54,159 --> 00:01:54,760
My money.

9
00:02:01,319 --> 00:02:02,120
Mine.

10
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:04,920
All mine.

11
00:02:16,639 --> 00:02:17,520
Take a break.

12
00:02:17,639 --> 00:02:18,639
Have some water, guys.

13
00:02:18,719 --> 00:02:19,879
I bought you something to eat.

14
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:41,479
Yu Ming.

15
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:44,120
Today, either you die

16
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,479
or I do.

17
00:03:15,479 --> 00:03:15,960
Sir.

18
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:18,719
He won't die here, will he?

19
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,080
No. No.

20
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,639
Look, his stomach is moving.

21
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:22,400
He is still breathing

22
00:03:22,599 --> 00:03:23,759
and smiling.

23
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:24,759
Relax. Relax.

24
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:25,879
Don't scare yourselves.

25
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,639
Four of us here

26
00:03:27,639 --> 00:03:28,319
draw too much attention.

27
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,599
You three go back first

28
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,879
and seal the tunnel.

29
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:31,599
Otherwise,

30
00:03:31,599 --> 00:03:32,280
our place will be like

31
00:03:32,319 --> 00:03:33,199
a public restroom.

32
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:34,599
Anyone could come in. Too dangerous.

33
00:03:34,759 --> 00:03:36,120
Leave this to me. No worries.

34
00:03:36,479 --> 00:03:37,000
Go.

35
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,080
Relax.

36
00:03:38,319 --> 00:03:38,680
Go.

37
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:39,560
Hurry.

38
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:43,000
Nurse.

39
00:03:43,439 --> 00:03:44,199
He passed out.

40
00:03:45,039 --> 00:03:45,840
Is he your friend?

41
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:46,759
No. I don't know him.

42
00:03:46,759 --> 00:03:48,000
I thought he was getting a perm.

43
00:03:48,039 --> 00:03:48,759
He just passed out.

44
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:49,439
Please help him.

45
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:50,840
Dr. Zhang. Dr. Zhang!

46
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:51,919
We have a head injury here.

47
00:03:51,919 --> 00:03:52,879
Sorry. I need to take this.

48
00:03:55,159 --> 00:03:55,800
Ms. Zhang.

49
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,599
Hey, Mr. Yu.

50
00:03:57,159 --> 00:03:57,879
I have been calling

51
00:03:57,879 --> 00:03:58,800
your wife, but cannot reach her.

52
00:03:59,120 --> 00:03:59,879
Where are you now?

53
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,360
Where are we?

54
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:03,360
After Baishi Service Area,

55
00:04:03,719 --> 00:04:04,759
stay on the Zhoumin Expressway,

56
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,240
take the second exit to the camp.

57
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,080
It is easy to find.

58
00:04:07,759 --> 00:04:08,479
Everyone is here.

59
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:09,639
Only you two.

60
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,120
Okay. Okay.

61
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,000
I got it.

62
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:12,520
Okay.

63
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,120
Ouyang.

64
00:04:21,439 --> 00:04:22,079
Listen to me.

65
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,759
Hong Jinkui found the tunnel,

66
00:04:23,759 --> 00:04:24,720
then crawled through it

67
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:25,720
into my house.

68
00:04:25,759 --> 00:04:27,240
He found the money too.

69
00:04:27,279 --> 00:04:27,839
Then he passed out.

70
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:29,319
So I brought him to the hospital.

71
00:04:29,399 --> 00:04:29,879
And now,

72
00:04:29,959 --> 00:04:31,000
Wenwen's teacher

73
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,120
needs Yitong and me there

74
00:04:32,199 --> 00:04:33,079
for some event.

75
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,360
I need you to back right now

76
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:35,160
and keep an eye on the money.

77
00:04:35,199 --> 00:04:36,120
I sent

78
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,040
three construction guys back

79
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:37,759
to fill the tunnel.

80
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:38,480
Get along with them.

81
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,319
You must protect

82
00:04:39,319 --> 00:04:39,839
that money.

83
00:04:39,879 --> 00:04:41,000
Some of it is Chen Zinuo's.

84
00:04:41,079 --> 00:04:41,800
Whether she wants it or not,

85
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:42,439
I will give it to her.

86
00:04:42,439 --> 00:04:43,639
Understand?

87
00:04:43,839 --> 00:04:45,319
So...

88
00:04:45,399 --> 00:04:46,519
Hurry up.

89
00:04:54,759 --> 00:04:55,720
What is this

90
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:56,319
half-day camp tour?

91
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:58,199
It is a half-day tour at a camp.

92
00:04:58,279 --> 00:05:00,000
Just the literal meaning?

93
00:05:01,399 --> 00:05:02,279
Where is it?

94
00:05:02,399 --> 00:05:03,639
Qiushan Resort.

95
00:05:03,839 --> 00:05:04,959
The students take the bus,

96
00:05:04,959 --> 00:05:07,360
and the parents drive there.

97
00:05:07,519 --> 00:05:08,680
Wenwen never told us.

98
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:09,680
Why is this so sudden?

99
00:05:10,079 --> 00:05:11,160
Maybe she feared

100
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:12,759
we'd embarrass her.

101
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:13,800
You are underestimating

102
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,040
your daughter.

103
00:05:15,079 --> 00:05:16,399
She isn't afraid of being embarrassed.

104
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:17,199
She's afraid that once we go,

105
00:05:17,199 --> 00:05:18,319
we will feel embarrassed.

106
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,360
She is protecting you.

107
00:05:19,519 --> 00:05:20,319
You understand nothing.

108
00:05:21,199 --> 00:05:21,800
Fine.

109
00:05:22,279 --> 00:05:23,480
Then I will show her

110
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,759
how strong we are.

111
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:27,879
How is Jiang Juan?

112
00:05:28,399 --> 00:05:29,480
I told her to go home and rest,

113
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:30,720
but my mom wouldn't let her.

114
00:05:30,959 --> 00:05:32,160
She was afraid of getting beaten.

115
00:05:32,279 --> 00:05:33,079
So now the two patients

116
00:05:33,079 --> 00:05:34,079
are taking care of each other.

117
00:05:34,079 --> 00:05:35,120
If you can call that care.

118
00:05:52,279 --> 00:05:52,759
San.

119
00:05:54,079 --> 00:05:54,680
What are you doing?

120
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,360
I was just thinking.

121
00:05:58,199 --> 00:05:59,399
When will we ever have

122
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,399
this much money?

123
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:01,519
Mr. Yu let us

124
00:06:01,519 --> 00:06:02,279
work here,

125
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:03,240
with the money right here.

126
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,399
That means he trusts us.

127
00:06:04,639 --> 00:06:05,839
Don't get any ideas.

128
00:06:06,439 --> 00:06:07,199
No way.

129
00:06:08,199 --> 00:06:08,720
Come here.

130
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:11,160
I was just saying.

131
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:27,600
Guys.

132
00:06:28,199 --> 00:06:29,079
There is noise upstairs.

133
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:29,959
Listen.

134
00:06:37,759 --> 00:06:38,319
Who are you?

135
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:39,759
I'm Yu Ming's friend.

136
00:06:39,759 --> 00:06:40,759
He sent me to help out.

137
00:06:41,319 --> 00:06:41,879
Okay.

138
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:43,040
Then come down.

139
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:44,360
I'm fine up here.

140
00:06:45,519 --> 00:06:46,399
A supervisor.

141
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:49,360
Get back to work.

142
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:17,800
Here, a big one.

143
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:18,480
You two share it.

144
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:18,959
Thanks, Dad.

145
00:07:18,959 --> 00:07:19,560
Don't share it with others.

146
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:22,720
Wenwen.

147
00:07:23,439 --> 00:07:23,959
Wenwen.

148
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:26,720
The steak is ready.

149
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:27,360
Have some.

150
00:07:27,759 --> 00:07:29,000
My dad grilled it. So good.

151
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,040
No.

152
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:31,720
Whatever.

153
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:34,959
Why are you here?

154
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:35,839
We wanted to have some fun too.

155
00:07:35,839 --> 00:07:37,160
Why did you leave us out?

156
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:40,199
Your dad's steak is good.

157
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:41,879
But he means too well.

158
00:07:41,879 --> 00:07:42,959
Just like the steak.

159
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,000
Overdone.

160
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,319
Too hard to swallow.

161
00:07:45,319 --> 00:07:46,000
Too tough.

162
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:47,560
Well, medium-well

163
00:07:47,639 --> 00:07:48,879
is not your taste, indeed.

164
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,360
You like it raw.

165
00:07:50,639 --> 00:07:52,000
Raw? Yeah. We eat people.

166
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,319
I believe that.

167
00:07:53,879 --> 00:07:55,000
You two

168
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:56,040
would absolutely do that.

169
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:56,800
Son.

170
00:07:57,199 --> 00:07:57,920
This family

171
00:07:57,959 --> 00:07:58,800
is kind of scary.

172
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,399
Come on. Let's go swimming.

173
00:08:00,959 --> 00:08:02,040
The teacher said no swimming here.

174
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,360
Did she say we should get eaten?

175
00:08:04,839 --> 00:08:05,560
Today,

176
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,439
I pass down to you

177
00:08:07,439 --> 00:08:09,000
our family title,

178
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:10,079
the Water Swift.

179
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,680
Water Swift?

180
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:14,519
More like Water Pig.

181
00:08:15,079 --> 00:08:16,000
What are you drawing?

182
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:18,600
Good.

183
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:19,680
The teeth are good.

184
00:08:20,519 --> 00:08:22,839
This beef is imported, actually.

185
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:23,920
It tastes good.

186
00:08:24,079 --> 00:08:24,759
Good?

187
00:08:24,759 --> 00:08:25,879
It is tough as leather.

188
00:08:25,879 --> 00:08:26,839
It is really not bad.

189
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:27,959
It has enough fat.

190
00:08:27,959 --> 00:08:28,399
Try it.

191
00:08:28,399 --> 00:08:28,920
No.

192
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:29,959
Wenwen, try it.

193
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,600
Eat it yourself.

194
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:33,600
Well, I misjudged him.

195
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,360
Son.

196
00:08:38,759 --> 00:08:40,000
This is freestyle.

197
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:45,480
On your back is backstroke.

198
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:48,720
You try.

199
00:08:49,159 --> 00:08:49,960
I'm scared.

200
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:51,519
I will show you a dive.

201
00:08:54,919 --> 00:08:55,399
Dad.

202
00:08:58,639 --> 00:08:59,360
Where is my watch?

203
00:08:59,879 --> 00:09:00,399
Oh no.

204
00:09:08,039 --> 00:09:08,799
Dad!

205
00:09:14,039 --> 00:09:14,679
Cramp!

206
00:09:14,759 --> 00:09:15,279
Dad!

207
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,440
What is wrong, Dad?

208
00:09:16,559 --> 00:09:18,000
Son, I have a cramp!

209
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,519
Help!

210
00:09:19,759 --> 00:09:20,840
Help my dad!

211
00:09:21,399 --> 00:09:22,639
Help!

212
00:09:22,799 --> 00:09:23,840
Help!

213
00:09:23,919 --> 00:09:24,960
Don't eat too much.

214
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:26,759
It would be a waste.

215
00:09:27,039 --> 00:09:28,759
Can't let the cow die for nothing.

216
00:09:29,519 --> 00:09:30,559
Help!

217
00:09:31,039 --> 00:09:31,759
Help!

218
00:09:31,799 --> 00:09:32,600
Want some seeds?

219
00:09:33,399 --> 00:09:34,519
Save my dad!

220
00:09:34,799 --> 00:09:36,000
Help!

221
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:36,879
What are you looking at?

222
00:09:36,879 --> 00:09:37,559
What happened over there?

223
00:09:37,679 --> 00:09:38,600
Help!

224
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:39,480
Save my dad!

225
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:50,799
Get more people.

226
00:09:50,919 --> 00:09:51,720
Have them pull the rope.

227
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:52,879
Someone, help!

228
00:09:53,039 --> 00:09:54,159
We need more hands!

229
00:09:54,519 --> 00:09:55,519
Come on, hurry!

230
00:09:55,519 --> 00:09:56,039
Someone fell in!

231
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:56,840
Hurry! Hurry!

232
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:57,919
Help! Help!

233
00:09:57,919 --> 00:09:58,960
Don't move! Stay here!

234
00:10:00,879 --> 00:10:02,080
Wenwen, stay still.

235
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:02,840
Yu Ming.

236
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,080
There is a rip current. Dangerous!

237
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:04,679
Come on!

238
00:10:04,879 --> 00:10:05,399
I can do it.

239
00:10:05,559 --> 00:10:06,639
Untie the rope.

240
00:10:06,679 --> 00:10:07,000
Yes.

241
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:07,759
Here!

242
00:10:07,799 --> 00:10:08,600
Don't tie it. No.

243
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:10,480
- Give it to me.
- Here.

244
00:10:10,559 --> 00:10:11,679
Let it out. Feed the line!

245
00:10:11,799 --> 00:10:12,639
Feed the line!

246
00:10:12,639 --> 00:10:13,320
- Yes.
- Okay.

247
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:20,879
Dad!

248
00:10:27,039 --> 00:10:27,799
Let it out!

249
00:10:27,799 --> 00:10:28,480
More, more!

250
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,559
Slowly.

251
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:30,519
It is okay.

252
00:10:30,519 --> 00:10:31,120
Your dad will be fine.

253
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,120
Slowly.

254
00:10:32,399 --> 00:10:33,000
Dad!

255
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:35,840
Help!

256
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:36,840
Save...

257
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:38,279
Save my son first!

258
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:41,080
Grab the life ring first.

259
00:10:41,919 --> 00:10:42,799
Save him!

260
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:44,080
Ring!

261
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:44,720
The ring!

262
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:51,159
He is almost up.

263
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:52,679
Careful!

264
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:57,600
Pull.

265
00:10:57,639 --> 00:10:58,159
Pull, pull!

266
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:00,480
Pull, pull!

267
00:11:00,559 --> 00:11:02,000
Pull harder! Come on!

268
00:11:02,279 --> 00:11:03,039
Dad!

269
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:05,120
Dad!

270
00:11:12,799 --> 00:11:13,519
Yu Ming!

271
00:11:13,679 --> 00:11:14,279
Dad!

272
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:15,759
Dad!

273
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:17,600
Dad!

274
00:11:18,519 --> 00:11:19,159
Dad!

275
00:11:19,919 --> 00:11:20,480
Hurry!

276
00:11:20,679 --> 00:11:21,440
The boy is up!

277
00:11:21,519 --> 00:11:22,320
We got the boy!

278
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:23,200
Come on, quick!

279
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:24,000
Slowly.

280
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:24,759
Slowly!

281
00:11:24,919 --> 00:11:25,759
- It's okay.
- Careful.

282
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:27,279
Get him back.

283
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,120
Dad!

284
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:52,399
Pull!

285
00:11:52,679 --> 00:11:53,039
Okay!

286
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:54,679
Pull! Hurry!

287
00:11:54,759 --> 00:11:55,559
Hold steady. Pull hard.

288
00:11:55,639 --> 00:11:56,000
Harder!

289
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:56,799
Pull it!

290
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:00,360
Yu Ming!

291
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:00,879
Dad!

292
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:02,360
Don't!

293
00:12:02,399 --> 00:12:02,799
Dad!

294
00:12:02,799 --> 00:12:03,200
It is dangerous!

295
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,080
He is not out yet!

296
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,080
- Dad!
- Yu Ming!

297
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:05,960
Don't go!

298
00:12:06,279 --> 00:12:07,200
Pull! Harder!

299
00:12:08,039 --> 00:12:08,879
You can't go!

300
00:12:08,919 --> 00:12:09,960
Pull up, then back!

301
00:12:11,559 --> 00:12:12,440
- He is up!
- Give us a hand!

302
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,000
Drag him up!

303
00:12:14,039 --> 00:12:14,440
Come on.

304
00:12:14,799 --> 00:12:15,879
Put him here.

305
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:19,080
Dad!

306
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:20,559
My husband is still in the water!

307
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,360
He's still in the water!

308
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:44,279
My brother is dead.

309
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,279
I should stay mute forever.

310
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,639
It hurts so much.

311
00:12:56,159 --> 00:12:58,039
So much.

312
00:12:58,679 --> 00:13:00,440
Why was the one who died

313
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:01,759
not me?

314
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:06,759
- Calm down!
- Dad!

315
00:13:06,799 --> 00:13:09,399
- Yu Ming!
- Dad! Dad!

316
00:13:11,639 --> 00:13:12,639
I will raise Wenwen

317
00:13:13,639 --> 00:13:15,320
as my own daughter

318
00:13:15,559 --> 00:13:16,679
and bring her up.

319
00:13:19,399 --> 00:13:21,440
Dad! Dad!

320
00:13:22,559 --> 00:13:24,159
Dad! Dad!

321
00:13:31,039 --> 00:13:31,679
Dad!

322
00:13:31,679 --> 00:13:32,279
Yu Ming!

323
00:13:32,279 --> 00:13:32,600
Dad!

324
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:33,759
There! His head is up!

325
00:13:34,559 --> 00:13:35,279
He is out!

326
00:13:35,279 --> 00:13:36,200
- Yu Ming!
- Dad!

327
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:36,559
Help him!

328
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:37,840
Dad!

329
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:39,120
Save him!

330
00:13:52,519 --> 00:13:53,639
Easy. Easy.

331
00:13:53,639 --> 00:13:54,679
Pull slowly. Easy.

332
00:13:54,679 --> 00:13:55,360
Easy.

333
00:13:59,399 --> 00:14:00,120
Come on!

334
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,159
Come on, pull!

335
00:14:35,639 --> 00:14:36,240
Did you think about

336
00:14:36,240 --> 00:14:37,519
what we would do if you died?

337
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:39,519
Did that ever cross your mind?

338
00:14:40,240 --> 00:14:41,679
I was trying to save them.

339
00:14:41,919 --> 00:14:43,600
I panicked and jumped in.

340
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:46,200
I mainly wanted to save the boy.

341
00:14:46,279 --> 00:14:46,960
That boy

342
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,120
is close to Wenwen

343
00:14:48,159 --> 00:14:48,960
and treats her well.

344
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:50,639
But I could not save the boy

345
00:14:50,799 --> 00:14:51,440
and leave his dad

346
00:14:51,519 --> 00:14:52,440
in there, could I?

347
00:14:52,799 --> 00:14:54,200
Do you know how your daughter

348
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:55,120
screamed on the beach?

349
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:56,200
I never want to hear

350
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:57,279
that sound again in my life.

351
00:14:57,399 --> 00:14:58,399
I hope you remember that.

352
00:14:58,639 --> 00:14:59,559
I will. I will.

353
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:00,600
It will not happen again.

354
00:15:02,759 --> 00:15:03,320
Wenwen.

355
00:15:03,919 --> 00:15:04,720
It's okay.

356
00:15:04,879 --> 00:15:05,960
Our family lives long.

357
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:07,519
We will all live to 140.

358
00:15:10,279 --> 00:15:11,039
There. There.

359
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:11,960
All right. All right.

360
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:13,200
No tears, okay?

361
00:15:14,799 --> 00:15:16,039
Don't be scared.

362
00:15:17,519 --> 00:15:19,159
Hello Kitty does not cry.

363
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,840
Why did you upset her?

364
00:15:35,879 --> 00:15:37,639
Ma'am, go sit down.

365
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:39,000
Just wait a bit.

366
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,159
The ribs are almost ready.

367
00:15:40,159 --> 00:15:41,159
I can handle this.

368
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:42,519
I'm fine.

369
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:43,759
Don't make me feel

370
00:15:44,159 --> 00:15:44,960
useless.

371
00:15:45,879 --> 00:15:46,919
I'm better now.

372
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:48,440
Strong as ever.

373
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:51,360
You just can't stop working.

374
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:52,600
You have been busy for years.

375
00:15:52,679 --> 00:15:53,480
Take a break.

376
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:55,360
I'm not as capable as you.

377
00:15:55,519 --> 00:15:56,720
Wait. I need to ask Jiajia.

378
00:15:59,159 --> 00:15:59,720
Jiajia.

379
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:01,519
Anything you don't eat?

380
00:16:01,919 --> 00:16:02,720
It's a little spicy.

381
00:16:02,919 --> 00:16:04,399
I eat everything. I can handle spice.

382
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:05,399
Okay.

383
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:08,240
He stayed under forever.

384
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:09,159
Wenwen and I

385
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:09,960
were standing on the shore,

386
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:10,840
calling and calling.

387
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:11,480
We kept shouting.

388
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:12,600
He was holding his breath in the water.

389
00:16:12,639 --> 00:16:13,559
We were holding ours on shore.

390
00:16:13,559 --> 00:16:14,600
No one dared to breathe.

391
00:16:14,639 --> 00:16:15,360
The way she screamed...

392
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:16,320
It was heartbreaking.

393
00:16:18,279 --> 00:16:19,320
When she came back, she went inside

394
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:20,519
and wouldn't say a word to her dad.

395
00:16:20,919 --> 00:16:21,399
I'm telling you,

396
00:16:21,399 --> 00:16:22,720
Yu Ming makes me so mad.

397
00:16:22,759 --> 00:16:24,240
He is going to be the death of me.

398
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:26,120
Why did he have to play hero?

399
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:27,320
What if he had not come back?

400
00:16:27,559 --> 00:16:28,399
Always acting tough.

401
00:16:28,399 --> 00:16:29,360
If he hadn't come back,

402
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:30,000
what would we do?

403
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:32,600
He has lost his mind!

404
00:17:00,279 --> 00:17:01,440
Still mad at your dad?

405
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:06,279
I would be too.

406
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:11,079
But you need to know

407
00:17:11,559 --> 00:17:12,960
that in that situation,

408
00:17:13,039 --> 00:17:14,559
what he did was right.

409
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:21,680
But you were

410
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:24,279
really scared of losing him.

411
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:28,519
Right?

412
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:33,839
I know you are angry right now.

413
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:36,680
And you have a lot to say to him.

414
00:17:37,759 --> 00:17:38,359
Go tell him.

415
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:39,200
Say it out.

416
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,279
Then you will not be so mad.

417
00:18:01,279 --> 00:18:02,279
I'm taking a shower.

418
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,440
I'm warning you.

419
00:18:03,559 --> 00:18:04,640
If you play hero again,

420
00:18:04,759 --> 00:18:05,839
I really will stop talking to you.

421
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,440
I will make Mom, Grandma,

422
00:18:07,519 --> 00:18:08,920
and my grandparents ignore you too.

423
00:18:09,079 --> 00:18:11,039
Even kids know self-protection.

424
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:12,160
You're an adult.

425
00:18:12,279 --> 00:18:13,279
Can you act like one?

426
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:15,000
Stop making everyone worry about you.

427
00:18:15,319 --> 00:18:17,119
If something really happened to you,

428
00:18:17,599 --> 00:18:19,079
I would support Mom remarrying.

429
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:19,960
Do you hear me?

430
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:29,000
Hurry up. Dad. I need you.

431
00:18:30,559 --> 00:18:31,359
Got it.

432
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:44,359
I wasn't joking earlier.

433
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:45,559
I know.

434
00:18:46,039 --> 00:18:47,200
I will be careful next time.

435
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:48,960
Not careful. Never again.

436
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:49,839
Okay.

437
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:50,680
Whatever you say.

438
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:56,359
What's wrong?

439
00:18:56,519 --> 00:18:57,599
I'm not feeling inspired.

440
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:00,279
I can draw monsters, not people.

441
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:02,039
Then I will call

442
00:19:02,079 --> 00:19:02,799
your mom over.

443
00:19:04,799 --> 00:19:06,319
The teacher said to draw our father.

444
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:07,759
You can draw me

445
00:19:07,759 --> 00:19:08,720
as a monster.

446
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:16,559
How about

447
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:18,240
you draw my brother?

448
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:19,759
Your biological father.

449
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:22,240
But I have no sense of him.

450
00:19:22,759 --> 00:19:24,200
You have seen his photos.

451
00:19:24,480 --> 00:19:26,559
I mean a feeling. A sense of him.

452
00:19:31,119 --> 00:19:32,519
He had

453
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:35,119
very bright eyes.

454
00:19:36,519 --> 00:19:37,160
No matter

455
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:38,720
where I was,

456
00:19:39,279 --> 00:19:41,359
he could spot me right away.

457
00:19:44,319 --> 00:19:46,680
He had such an easy smile.

458
00:19:48,599 --> 00:19:50,039
With bright white teeth.

459
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:53,319
Congratulations, bro.

460
00:19:53,319 --> 00:19:54,519
You have a little niece now.

461
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,359
I have a little niece!

462
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:57,279
When you have a concert,

463
00:19:57,480 --> 00:19:58,440
we will sit in the front row.

464
00:19:58,759 --> 00:20:00,160
We'll hold up your banner and shout,

465
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:01,920
"Yu Ming, I love you!"

466
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:02,680
Keep it down. Feng.

467
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:04,119
"You sing so well!"

468
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:04,680
Like that?

469
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:06,920
Not sharp teeth.

470
00:20:07,359 --> 00:20:08,200
Round.

471
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:15,880
When I was little,

472
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:17,480
I was not very confident.

473
00:20:18,519 --> 00:20:20,200
He would always encourage me.

474
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:22,039
When I was bad at sports,

475
00:20:22,559 --> 00:20:23,880
he would tell me

476
00:20:24,039 --> 00:20:25,200
I was good at singing.

477
00:20:26,079 --> 00:20:27,599
When I was bad at math,

478
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:30,079
he would still tell me

479
00:20:30,119 --> 00:20:31,200
I was good at singing.

480
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:34,079
When I was short,

481
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:37,160
he still said I sang well.

482
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,440
Because he kept encouraging me,

483
00:20:39,559 --> 00:20:40,960
I became more and more confident.

484
00:20:41,160 --> 00:20:41,839
In the end,

485
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,440
I became a singer.

486
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:46,680
People liked hearing me sing.

487
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:48,799
And I was happy.

488
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:50,960
Then later,

489
00:20:51,359 --> 00:20:52,680
I got full of myself.

490
00:20:53,359 --> 00:20:54,160
I bought

491
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:55,640
all those weird clothes,

492
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:56,920
ripped jeans,

493
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,039
and ragged outfits.

494
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:00,839
Your grandparents hated it.

495
00:21:01,759 --> 00:21:03,720
The neighbors disliked me, too.

496
00:21:04,319 --> 00:21:06,319
But he encouraged me again.

497
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:08,119
He said,

498
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,400
"While you are young,

499
00:21:09,480 --> 00:21:10,240
be yourself.

500
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,200
When you are old,

501
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:13,960
you will not have the energy."

502
00:21:15,160 --> 00:21:15,799
This is for you.

503
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:17,200
Thank you.

504
00:21:21,279 --> 00:21:22,039
Sometimes I wonder,

505
00:21:22,519 --> 00:21:24,079
he was young too back then.

506
00:21:24,799 --> 00:21:26,160
How was he so amazing,

507
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:27,480
so smart?

508
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:30,079
He always knew

509
00:21:30,519 --> 00:21:31,519
what I was thinking

510
00:21:32,279 --> 00:21:33,079
and what I wanted.

511
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:34,640
But

512
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:36,680
I never once thought about

513
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:38,000
what he wanted.

514
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:40,680
Maybe

515
00:21:41,319 --> 00:21:42,759
all he wanted was for us

516
00:21:43,079 --> 00:21:43,839
to be happy.

517
00:21:44,799 --> 00:21:46,279
He was very, very kind.

518
00:21:47,119 --> 00:21:48,720
He always wanted to help others.

519
00:21:49,559 --> 00:21:50,079
So,

520
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:52,519
if he had been there

521
00:21:52,799 --> 00:21:53,559
today,

522
00:21:54,359 --> 00:21:55,559
he would have done the same.

523
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,440
So he rubbed off on you.

524
00:22:00,079 --> 00:22:00,759
Of course.

525
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,519
I'm his little brother.

526
00:22:03,359 --> 00:22:04,839
And he was my big brother.

527
00:22:05,279 --> 00:22:07,119
My hero, always.

528
00:22:15,519 --> 00:22:16,000
She is asleep?

529
00:22:16,079 --> 00:22:16,519
Yes.

530
00:22:17,039 --> 00:22:17,440
Good.

531
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:40,880
Jiajia, we have something to say.

532
00:22:47,759 --> 00:22:49,119
The 60 million is untouched?

533
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:49,880
Not a cent.

534
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:53,240
You really want my advice?

535
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:55,160
Yes.

536
00:23:00,319 --> 00:23:00,839
Tell the police.

537
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:19,119
Jiajia is right.

538
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,519
Living on edge every day

539
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:23,559
is too much pressure.

540
00:23:25,519 --> 00:23:27,200
If we drag this out,

541
00:23:28,079 --> 00:23:29,119
it will only get worse.

542
00:23:31,119 --> 00:23:32,920
Once the police come to us,

543
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:34,160
it's too late.

544
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:37,359
Then the whole thing changes.

545
00:23:38,759 --> 00:23:40,400
Hiding that money

546
00:23:41,599 --> 00:23:42,920
feels like carrying a boulder.

547
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:44,920
It's exhausting.

548
00:23:45,759 --> 00:23:47,440
I want this weight gone.

549
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:49,519
Even if not for ourselves,

550
00:23:50,480 --> 00:23:52,119
we have to think of our family.

551
00:23:53,279 --> 00:23:54,279
Let's turn ourselves in.

552
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,279
I agree.

553
00:23:58,440 --> 00:23:59,720
We will find Guo Li tomorrow

554
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:01,720
and tell her everything.

555
00:24:45,599 --> 00:24:47,279
Couldn't we just text him?

556
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:48,839
Why write a letter?

557
00:24:50,799 --> 00:24:51,759
It's different.

558
00:24:52,599 --> 00:24:53,480
When Dad reads

559
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:54,839
this letter,

560
00:24:55,799 --> 00:24:57,200
he can feel

561
00:24:58,079 --> 00:25:00,200
the warmth of our regret.

562
00:25:02,440 --> 00:25:04,119
What are you going to write?

563
00:25:04,559 --> 00:25:05,839
I haven't figured it all out.

564
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:07,400
Right now,

565
00:25:08,519 --> 00:25:09,759
all I can think of is,

566
00:25:12,039 --> 00:25:12,640
"Dad,

567
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:16,440
by the time you read this,

568
00:25:18,039 --> 00:25:19,319
we will already be in custody."

569
00:25:24,759 --> 00:25:25,200
Okay.

570
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:27,720
"If we don't come out,

571
00:25:28,880 --> 00:25:30,319
please take care of Wenwen."

572
00:25:31,799 --> 00:25:32,799
That is all I have so far.

573
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:34,039
Add one more line.

574
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:36,240
"If the old woman starts trouble,

575
00:25:36,839 --> 00:25:38,279
you must step in.

576
00:25:38,519 --> 00:25:39,200
Remember that."

577
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:41,440
Maybe not "old woman" here.

578
00:25:41,920 --> 00:25:43,440
Calling her "Mom"

579
00:25:43,440 --> 00:25:44,720
would sound warmer.

580
00:25:45,039 --> 00:25:45,720
Fine.

581
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:10,839
I'll go buy another one.

582
00:26:25,319 --> 00:26:25,759
I need this file

583
00:26:25,799 --> 00:26:26,920
by two this afternoon.

584
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:27,440
Okay.

585
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:30,559
Okay, thanks.

586
00:26:32,559 --> 00:26:33,359
Did you check the surveil...?

587
00:26:33,359 --> 00:26:33,799
Guo Li.

588
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:35,079
Wait.

589
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:37,920
She's busy. Hold on.

590
00:26:38,799 --> 00:26:39,759
Tell me,

591
00:26:39,920 --> 00:26:40,759
can you blame us for this?

592
00:26:40,920 --> 00:26:42,599
It's obviously the bank's fault.

593
00:26:42,720 --> 00:26:43,640
An ATM suddenly

594
00:26:43,640 --> 00:26:44,759
spits out over 200 grand.

595
00:26:44,920 --> 00:26:46,000
Anyone would lose their head.

596
00:26:46,319 --> 00:26:47,559
Of course you take it.

597
00:26:48,039 --> 00:26:49,400
After my wife took it,

598
00:26:49,599 --> 00:26:51,279
the money was barely in our hands

599
00:26:51,359 --> 00:26:52,559
before they called it theft.

600
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:54,279
They say she could get 4 or 5 years.

601
00:26:54,319 --> 00:26:55,160
If she really goes in,

602
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:56,240
what are we supposed to do?

603
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:58,680
That is nothing.

604
00:26:59,079 --> 00:26:59,759
Her brother-in-law

605
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:00,920
rented a small storefront

606
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:02,039
as a parcel station.

607
00:27:02,640 --> 00:27:04,240
People always forget their packages.

608
00:27:04,839 --> 00:27:05,640
There was one package

609
00:27:05,680 --> 00:27:06,680
that sat there for months.

610
00:27:06,880 --> 00:27:08,400
He was afraid it would mold,

611
00:27:08,519 --> 00:27:09,559
so he kindly took it home

612
00:27:09,759 --> 00:27:11,400
to keep it safe for the owner.

613
00:27:11,920 --> 00:27:13,799
Who knew it was a luxury watch?

614
00:27:14,200 --> 00:27:15,240
Worth over a million.

615
00:27:15,599 --> 00:27:16,799
Now, the owner called the police,

616
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:18,000
saying he took the watch.

617
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:19,640
The police are investigating.

618
00:27:20,119 --> 00:27:20,799
Unbelievable!

619
00:27:20,839 --> 00:27:21,599
What are you two here for?

620
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:24,039
Well, I...

621
00:27:24,079 --> 00:27:24,680
I have...

622
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:28,319
Hello?

623
00:27:29,359 --> 00:27:29,960
What?

624
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:30,799
Five million?

625
00:27:31,359 --> 00:27:32,680
That's an extremely large amount.

626
00:27:33,319 --> 00:27:35,119
Ask a lawyer about the sentence.

627
00:27:35,519 --> 00:27:36,359
Based on past cases,

628
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:37,200
at least ten years.

629
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:39,240
We give anti-fraud talks every day

630
00:27:39,240 --> 00:27:40,079
and explain the legal consequences.

631
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:40,680
Why do these people

632
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:41,559
never listen?

633
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:43,079
Okay. I will ask for you.

634
00:27:53,799 --> 00:27:54,599
That is terrifying.

635
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:55,599
60 million

636
00:27:55,599 --> 00:27:56,920
could get us shot several times.

637
00:27:59,880 --> 00:28:06,880
♪I shouldn't have shown off
before heaven.♪

638
00:28:07,559 --> 00:28:12,960
♪I shouldn't have wrecked
the peach feast.♪

639
00:28:13,599 --> 00:28:17,599
♪Now I suffer beneath the mountain,♪

640
00:28:17,839 --> 00:28:20,119
♪only now knowing Buddha's power♪

641
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,799
♪reaches beyond the heavens.♪

642
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:23,440
What's wrong?

643
00:28:26,480 --> 00:28:27,039
What?

644
00:28:28,319 --> 00:28:29,440
Nothing. I have a cramp.

645
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:30,960
You scared me.

646
00:28:35,359 --> 00:28:36,160
When I was little,

647
00:28:37,319 --> 00:28:38,519
I stole money from my mom

648
00:28:39,559 --> 00:28:40,480
to buy a toy.

649
00:28:40,880 --> 00:28:41,640
I got it.

650
00:28:43,079 --> 00:28:43,720
The whole way,

651
00:28:44,599 --> 00:28:45,960
I ran toward the market.

652
00:28:46,400 --> 00:28:47,200
But as I ran,

653
00:28:47,480 --> 00:28:48,119
I got more anxious,

654
00:28:48,599 --> 00:28:49,400
more scared.

655
00:28:50,599 --> 00:28:52,039
I realized the fear

656
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:52,880
was far greater

657
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:54,079
than the joy of buying the toy.

658
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:55,599
So,

659
00:28:56,119 --> 00:28:57,680
I turned around and ran home.

660
00:28:58,200 --> 00:28:59,319
I put the money back.

661
00:29:00,279 --> 00:29:01,000
To this day,

662
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:03,119
my mom still doesn't know it.

663
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:07,039
How about this?

664
00:29:07,759 --> 00:29:09,440
We haven't touched the money,

665
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:10,000
right?

666
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:11,200
We put back

667
00:29:11,519 --> 00:29:13,119
what was in the wall

668
00:29:13,240 --> 00:29:13,920
and rebury

669
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:14,960
what was underground.

670
00:29:15,319 --> 00:29:16,039
That way,

671
00:29:16,839 --> 00:29:17,559
we can pretend

672
00:29:18,039 --> 00:29:19,480
none of this ever happened.

673
00:29:32,759 --> 00:29:33,400
It just started boiling.

674
00:29:37,240 --> 00:29:38,160
Look at you,

675
00:29:38,240 --> 00:29:38,880
having hot pot alone

676
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:40,000
in the basement.

677
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:41,400
How could I be alone?

678
00:29:41,759 --> 00:29:43,039
This is my assistant, Money.

679
00:29:43,319 --> 00:29:43,960
Yo, man.

680
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:45,079
Money. Money.

681
00:29:45,319 --> 00:29:46,400
I'm here.

682
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:47,240
Say hello.

683
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:48,119
Hello.

684
00:29:48,279 --> 00:29:49,640
How can I help you?

685
00:29:49,799 --> 00:29:50,519
He has lost it.

686
00:29:50,599 --> 00:29:51,559
I was bored.

687
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:56,920
Unbelievable!

688
00:29:57,720 --> 00:29:58,480
No integrity.

689
00:29:58,559 --> 00:30:00,119
I saw that whole room full of cash.

690
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:00,759
You don't pay me back,

691
00:30:00,799 --> 00:30:01,759
but you sent someone to set me up?

692
00:30:01,880 --> 00:30:02,319
Scum.

693
00:30:02,359 --> 00:30:03,240
Scumbag!

694
00:30:05,759 --> 00:30:06,880
Watch your mouth!

695
00:30:07,240 --> 00:30:08,359
Have some manners!

696
00:30:11,160 --> 00:30:11,960
Who are you talking to?

697
00:30:12,839 --> 00:30:13,720
Who has no manners?

698
00:30:13,839 --> 00:30:14,519
You.

699
00:30:14,680 --> 00:30:15,720
This is a hospital, not your home.

700
00:30:15,839 --> 00:30:16,720
Keep it down!

701
00:30:16,839 --> 00:30:18,039
This is the way I talk.

702
00:30:18,039 --> 00:30:19,039
None of your business.

703
00:30:19,039 --> 00:30:19,839
It is my business.

704
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:20,720
You little punk.

705
00:30:20,720 --> 00:30:21,359
Say it again?

706
00:30:21,359 --> 00:30:22,119
- Come here!
- My fault!

707
00:30:22,119 --> 00:30:22,960
- Come on!
- My bad!

708
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:23,400
I wouldn't dare.

709
00:30:23,400 --> 00:30:23,880
Say it again!

710
00:30:23,880 --> 00:30:24,440
I said I wouldn't dare.

711
00:30:24,440 --> 00:30:25,160
Come here!

712
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:29,160
So rude.

713
00:30:29,799 --> 00:30:31,000
Everyone can push me around.

714
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:32,279
Just because I stay quiet,

715
00:30:32,279 --> 00:30:33,799
you think I'm a pushover?

716
00:30:34,079 --> 00:30:35,079
Once I get rich this time,

717
00:30:35,440 --> 00:30:36,359
I will make you all pay.

718
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:37,480
I will buy a villa.

719
00:30:37,599 --> 00:30:38,279
A huge one.

720
00:30:38,319 --> 00:30:39,319
I will buy a jet and a yacht.

721
00:30:39,480 --> 00:30:40,319
When I fly first class,

722
00:30:40,319 --> 00:30:40,960
I will buy two seats

723
00:30:41,480 --> 00:30:42,400
and sleep all the way I want.

724
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:43,440
When I'm rich,

725
00:30:43,640 --> 00:30:44,480
you're all dead.

726
00:30:45,079 --> 00:30:45,720
Yu Ming.

727
00:30:46,079 --> 00:30:46,880
I'll kill you!

728
00:30:52,920 --> 00:30:54,119
Yu Ming,

729
00:30:54,559 --> 00:30:57,440
screw you!

730
00:31:04,440 --> 00:31:04,920
Yu Ming!

731
00:31:05,680 --> 00:31:06,200
Yu Ming!

732
00:31:06,519 --> 00:31:07,319
Open the door!

733
00:31:07,319 --> 00:31:08,279
I'm here to make you pay!

734
00:31:08,519 --> 00:31:09,039
Yu Ming!

735
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:10,240
Yu Ming! Open the door!

736
00:31:10,359 --> 00:31:11,400
Come out and talk to me.

737
00:31:11,519 --> 00:31:12,759
I'm here today

738
00:31:12,759 --> 00:31:13,319
to die with you.

739
00:31:13,359 --> 00:31:14,079
We shall perish together.

740
00:31:14,319 --> 00:31:15,240
Come on. Come out!

741
00:31:15,240 --> 00:31:16,240
If he wants to curse,

742
00:31:17,160 --> 00:31:18,039
why throw in fancy words?

743
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:19,559
Makes him feel educated.

744
00:31:20,880 --> 00:31:21,640
This money,

745
00:31:21,799 --> 00:31:22,839
we have to

746
00:31:22,839 --> 00:31:23,759
find out where it came from.

747
00:31:23,839 --> 00:31:24,519
Otherwise,

748
00:31:24,920 --> 00:31:26,240
we may die without knowing why.

749
00:31:26,319 --> 00:31:27,480
So what we know now is

750
00:31:28,079 --> 00:31:28,960
that the money involves

751
00:31:29,039 --> 00:31:29,519
Hu Deshuai,

752
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:30,279
the construction workers,

753
00:31:30,319 --> 00:31:31,599
and Zinuo and her mother.

754
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:32,880
Yu Ming, open the door!

755
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:34,079
I'm here for you!

756
00:31:34,160 --> 00:31:35,400
Hu Deshuai is already dead.

757
00:31:35,799 --> 00:31:36,640
Those three construction workers

758
00:31:36,640 --> 00:31:37,440
don't seem fake.

759
00:31:37,559 --> 00:31:39,200
The papers they had,

760
00:31:39,359 --> 00:31:40,559
all those signatures,

761
00:31:40,599 --> 00:31:41,400
the creases,

762
00:31:41,519 --> 00:31:42,680
the aged look,

763
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:43,839
they looked old.

764
00:31:44,519 --> 00:31:45,400
They didn't look fake.

765
00:31:45,599 --> 00:31:46,319
Open the door, Yu Ming!

766
00:31:46,359 --> 00:31:47,480
I'm here for you!

767
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:49,559
What are you looking at?

768
00:31:49,799 --> 00:31:50,640
You are disturbing everyone.

769
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:51,480
Do you know that?

770
00:31:51,519 --> 00:31:52,319
Then call the police.

771
00:31:52,440 --> 00:31:53,000
Better yet,

772
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:54,000
go get the TV reporters

773
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:54,559
over here.

774
00:31:54,599 --> 00:31:55,480
Thank you very much!

775
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:56,319
So unreasonable.

776
00:31:56,359 --> 00:31:56,880
Yu Ming!

777
00:31:57,200 --> 00:31:58,319
Yu Ming, open up for me.

778
00:31:58,319 --> 00:31:58,799
Yu Ming!

779
00:31:58,839 --> 00:32:00,079
Open the door!

780
00:32:00,200 --> 00:32:02,079
Yu Ming, open up!

781
00:32:02,279 --> 00:32:03,119
Yu Ming!

782
00:32:03,240 --> 00:32:04,359
Yu Ming!

783
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:05,559
So now,

784
00:32:05,839 --> 00:32:06,759
people who may know the truth

785
00:32:06,759 --> 00:32:07,880
are Chen Zinuo and her mom,

786
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:08,279
right?

787
00:32:09,119 --> 00:32:09,759
I think

788
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:11,160
we shouldn't ask her mom.

789
00:32:11,359 --> 00:32:12,359
She looks too vicious.

790
00:32:12,559 --> 00:32:13,720
Like a hungry she-wolf

791
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:14,720
on a rainy night.

792
00:32:15,079 --> 00:32:16,079
Chen Zinuo is much better.

793
00:32:16,160 --> 00:32:17,000
Her eyes

794
00:32:17,119 --> 00:32:18,720
are like a curious

795
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:20,240
baby seal.

796
00:32:21,160 --> 00:32:22,000
Let's ask her.

797
00:32:28,079 --> 00:32:28,680
Me?

798
00:32:29,519 --> 00:32:30,079
Who else?

799
00:32:30,559 --> 00:32:31,960
Aren't you her future boyfriend?

800
00:32:32,559 --> 00:32:33,400
No.

801
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:34,920
But if she confesses to me,

802
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:35,720
I may consider it.

803
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:39,160
How can you prove you own the place?

804
00:32:39,359 --> 00:32:40,319
I have my ID.

805
00:32:40,359 --> 00:32:40,960
Let me see it.

806
00:32:41,079 --> 00:32:42,000
My ID is inside.

807
00:32:42,240 --> 00:32:43,000
Without an ID,

808
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:43,920
how can I open the door?

809
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:45,319
Open the door first.

810
00:32:45,359 --> 00:32:46,480
I will get my ID

811
00:32:46,480 --> 00:32:47,160
and show it to you.

812
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:48,079
Then you will know

813
00:32:48,119 --> 00:32:48,720
I'm the owner.

814
00:32:48,839 --> 00:32:50,160
You have no proof.

815
00:32:50,359 --> 00:32:51,160
I can't open it.

816
00:32:51,279 --> 00:32:52,480
I have to call property management

817
00:32:52,519 --> 00:32:53,039
and check.

818
00:32:53,039 --> 00:32:53,720
Check what?

819
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:54,319
Why call anyone?

820
00:32:54,319 --> 00:32:55,640
What are you, the police?

821
00:32:55,720 --> 00:32:56,759
This is my house.

822
00:32:56,799 --> 00:32:58,480
I filed a police report on it.

823
00:32:58,519 --> 00:33:00,119
Are you trying to get me fired?

824
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:00,759
What...

825
00:33:01,119 --> 00:33:01,559
Hey!

826
00:33:01,559 --> 00:33:02,400
You! The property girl!

827
00:33:02,400 --> 00:33:03,359
Come here.

828
00:33:03,559 --> 00:33:04,200
What was your name again?

829
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:05,799
Zhao... Zhao Xiaolin, right?

830
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:06,400
Jiang Xiaoling.

831
00:33:06,519 --> 00:33:07,839
Whatever. Come here.

832
00:33:08,119 --> 00:33:09,039
Tell him.

833
00:33:09,559 --> 00:33:10,079
Tell him

834
00:33:10,119 --> 00:33:11,599
whether I own Unit 505.

835
00:33:12,519 --> 00:33:13,240
He used to.

836
00:33:13,279 --> 00:33:13,759
Used to?

837
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:14,839
What do you mean, used to?

838
00:33:14,920 --> 00:33:16,000
Didn't I just pay you

839
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:17,319
the property management fees
for this place?

840
00:33:17,880 --> 00:33:18,440
Back fees.

841
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:19,839
I still paid them,

842
00:33:19,839 --> 00:33:20,279
didn't I?

843
00:33:20,319 --> 00:33:20,759
Open it.

844
00:33:20,759 --> 00:33:21,839
Come on. Open it.

845
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:23,880
Please don't, Mr. Hong.

846
00:33:24,160 --> 00:33:25,640
Your house has been sold.

847
00:33:25,759 --> 00:33:27,079
You are no longer the owner.

848
00:33:27,599 --> 00:33:28,519
So what you mean is,

849
00:33:28,599 --> 00:33:29,799
I'm not

850
00:33:29,799 --> 00:33:31,079
the owner anymore, right?

851
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:32,240
Fine. Easy.

852
00:33:32,279 --> 00:33:33,440
Then refund
my property management fees.

853
00:33:33,640 --> 00:33:34,000
Right?

854
00:33:34,079 --> 00:33:34,599
Come on. Refund me.

855
00:33:34,759 --> 00:33:35,440
Pay me back.

856
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:36,640
No refund?

857
00:33:36,759 --> 00:33:37,400
Then open the door.

858
00:33:37,480 --> 00:33:37,920
Come on.

859
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:38,640
Sir.

860
00:33:38,680 --> 00:33:39,720
You are not the owner anymore.

861
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:40,480
I can't help you.

862
00:33:40,480 --> 00:33:41,319
Fine. I don't need you.

863
00:33:41,319 --> 00:33:42,000
I will handle it myself.

864
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:42,960
Hey, stop!

865
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:44,319
Mr. Hong, you cannot do that.

866
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:45,880
Or I have to call the police.

867
00:33:46,319 --> 00:33:46,799
Go ahead.

868
00:33:47,599 --> 00:33:48,599
Call them or not,

869
00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:49,759
I'm opening my own door.

870
00:33:49,759 --> 00:33:50,799
What is wrong with that?

871
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:51,960
There are cameras everywhere.

872
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:53,920
If you pick the lock,

873
00:33:54,359 --> 00:33:56,359
we have to call the police.

874
00:34:00,839 --> 00:34:01,680
Fine.

875
00:34:02,720 --> 00:34:03,279
Here.

876
00:34:12,719 --> 00:34:14,000
Can't I rest here for a bit?

877
00:34:16,639 --> 00:34:17,320
I'm dizzy.

878
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:18,719
I'll sit here for a while.

879
00:34:24,159 --> 00:34:24,679
Mr. Hong.

880
00:34:24,840 --> 00:34:25,960
You may rest here.

881
00:34:26,039 --> 00:34:26,599
But

882
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:29,239
there are cameras all around.

883
00:34:30,639 --> 00:34:31,119
Well,

884
00:34:32,559 --> 00:34:33,199
we will

885
00:34:33,639 --> 00:34:34,320
get going.

886
00:34:44,360 --> 00:34:45,239
It's Zinuo's birthday today.

887
00:34:45,280 --> 00:34:45,800
I have to go.

888
00:34:46,440 --> 00:34:47,000
Wait.

889
00:34:48,079 --> 00:34:49,000
That fat guy in black

890
00:34:49,079 --> 00:34:50,079
is still sitting outside.

891
00:34:50,599 --> 00:34:51,119
What do I do then?

892
00:35:00,599 --> 00:35:01,880
Yu Ming, open the door!

893
00:35:02,199 --> 00:35:02,880
You scum!

894
00:35:02,880 --> 00:35:03,880
I know you are home, Yu Ming!

895
00:35:03,920 --> 00:35:05,119
I'll take you out from the second floor.

896
00:35:08,199 --> 00:35:09,480
Unbelievable! Yu Ming!

897
00:35:11,960 --> 00:35:12,559
Yu Ming!

898
00:35:13,320 --> 00:35:13,960
